TWO-FLUID 2D HYDROSTATIC TEST WITH MIXED CELLS
----------------------------------------------

Two inviscid fluids at rest in a [-5,5]^2 domain subject to gravity; lighter
fluid on top. Fluid should remain at rest, with a linear pressure field.

With g=(0,-1,0): rho2 = 2, p = -2*y + c, in y < 1/2;
                 rho1 = 1, p = -y - 0.5 + c, in y > 1/2.

Fluid interface placed at cell midpoint.

Variations use rotated meshes (and rotated g)

&OUTPUTS
  output_t  = 0.0, 2.0
  output_dt = 2.0
/

&MESH
  mesh_file = 'mesh2-rotz.gen'
/

&PHYSICS
  materials = 'water', 'oil'
  legacy_flow = .true.
  body_force_density = 0.707106781186547, -0.707106781186547, 0.0
/

&NUMERICS
  dt_constant = 0.125
  discrete_ops_type           = 'ortho'
/

&LEGACY_FLOW
  inviscid   = .true.
  projection_linear_solution  = 'projection'
  body_force_face_method      = .true.
  courant_number              = 0.5
/

&LINEAR_SOLVER
  name = 'projection'
  method = 'fgmres'
  preconditioning_method = 'ssor'
  convergence_criterion = 1.0e-12
  relaxation_parameter = 1.4
  preconditioning_steps = 2
  maximum_iterations = 200
/

# FREE SLIP BC ALL AROUND

Lower half
&BODY
  surface_name = 'plane'
  axis = 'y'
  fill = 'outside'
  rotation_angle = 0, 0, 45
  translation_pt = -0.353553390593274, 0.3535533905932747, 0.0 ! 1/(2*sqrt(2))
  mesh_material_number = 1
  material_name = 'water'
  velocity = 3*0.0
  temperature = 0.0
/


upper half
&BODY
  surface_name = 'background'
  material_name = 'oil'
  velocity = 3*0.0
  temperature = 0.0
/

&MATERIAL
  name = 'water'
  is_fluid = T
  density = 2.0
  specific_heat = 1.0
/

&MATERIAL
  name = 'oil'
  is_fluid = T
  density = 1.0
  specific_heat = 1.0
/
